ReviewText:
Ever since I couldnt get my Nescafe Gold Blend 37 , I have been looking for an equally delicious and strong intense coffee and I think I have found it. 
For a granular coffee this really does match up to the real bean experience so much so my mother and friends all buy it now after sampling mine. Intenso by name, intenso by nature this truly is a revelation in coffee - Top marks Nescafe!
Title: Best coffee granules on the market

ReviewText: I am generally a filter and dolce gusto coffee drinker and don't really like instant. But I have friends who don't like real coffee so it's easy to throw a spoonful of instant in a cup for them, I thought I'd try some Azera on them for a change but before doing so I had to try a cup myself and I found it surprisingly good. It won't change my preferences but if I'm in a hurry I'll be more than happy to have a cup, and I'll try a different variety next time.
Title: Surprisingly good

ReviewText: Bought this last month as a change from using a French Press coffee maker and all the fuss of grinding beans, brewing, filtering and then disposing of the grounds and it tastes even better. Value for money, it could not be beaten, watch out for special offers and stock up. This tastes just like the real think but no hassle and made in seconds. Intense, strong but with not a hint of bitterness.
Title: Real coffee flavour without all the fuss!!

ReviewText: My 30 year old Son only drinks Freshly Ground or Fresh Barrista coffee. Personally I have been drinking Azera Intenso for the last six months.  One cup of Azera and he was hooked; claiming it was the best "Proper Coffee" he had ever tasted.  Its rich roast, its fine quality and great value for money, means he wont change back! would You?
Title: Fooled! and Converted!

ReviewText: I brought this coffee because of all the advertising that I had seen. I drink a lot of coffee so I thought I need to find out if it is as good as the advertising says it is. I brought some and..... wow..... it really is that good. I would recommend this coffee to anyone without fear that they would not agree with me. Well done Nescafe.
Title: Wow factor

ReviewText: Love my Nescafé Azeri intenso, first thing every morning!
Title: Get up and go!

ReviewText:
First experienced this coffee at my Sisters and for the first time ever asked someone where they bought there coffee.
Regular user now. I find just over a teaspoon with a good 'glug' of warm milk gives a great taste. 
I need to try the other flavours but can't be dragged away just yet.
Title: Delicious coffee taste

ReviewText: I am a true coffee lover and have a machine at home . I love the taste and smell of fresh coffee brewing. Imagine my surprise when I bought  Nescafe Azera Intenso thinking I would have to "make do" with instant coffee. No not at all, it was as good as freshly brewed coffee. This is definitely my GO TO coffee from now on .Well done Nescafe. I will definitely try the Azera full range.
Title: Just like the real thing

ReviewText: So at work they 'club together' for tea, coffee, milk and biscuits. Do I put into this fund ..... emm No! Maybe it's because I take my coffe black, maybe I have high standards but  the stuff they drink is dire. This is my luxury it gets me through the day. Strong and full bodied with a great aroma too
Title: Just Mine!

ReviewText: Love the rounded but punchy aspect of this coffee. I especially like the limited edition tins by design: 'Hustle and Bustle' is the one I'm drinking this morning. I've a busy day ahead but a quiet moment with good coffee and I'm seeing hustle and bustle as a good thing.
Title: Instantly Invigorating

ReviewText: Love this coffee.  I have been buying it for a few months now and it is lovely,  really smooth and gives you that much needed morning boost.  We love it so much we even took a tin on holiday with us to the carribbean as we were worried we couldn't manage without it!
Title: As good as the coffee shops

ReviewText:
I bought a tin of this coffee for a change to the usual ripoff coffees that you get from a coffee shop.
The taste is great, especially as I like a very strong tasting coffee.
Would definitely recommend this coffee if you're looking for something instant.
Title: Smooth intense taste

ReviewText: I like my coffee strong and prefer a freshly brewed cuppa and only used instant coffee when in a hurry. But then I discovered Nescafe Azera and all that changed. I like the Intenso, and I even serve it to visitors without them realising that it is instant.
Title: Just as good as freshly brewed

ReviewText: I have always been a huge fan on Nescafe Gold Blend and thought I would try this for a change and I am hooked!  I love the intense smooth flavour and aroma.  The packaging is fantastic too!  You know it's going to be a high quality product.
Title: A treat in a tin!

ReviewText: Bought recently as I was fed up with poor tasting coffee.  What a fantastic cup thhis made, hard to resist a second one shortly after, so full of flavour, I work from home andd need to be on the ball, this is the perfect pick me up
Title: Wow, a coffee to enjoy

ReviewText: Lucky to come across this gorgeous coffee in a free hamper I got from work at Christmas. Between the Intenso and the Americano I've developed a taste for coffee now and tea jist doesn't cut the mustard anymore
Title: Exquisite and Ultra smooth

ReviewText: I have bought this since it arrived on shelves.  This fresh ground tasting coffee beats all others of its type hands down.  This to me is THE ONLY coffee that matches aroma with quality taste.  Perfection!
Title: Aroma matches taste!!!!

ReviewText: This is a very tasty and coffee and keeps me going through my morning! I have only recently started drinking coffee and I find this delicious. I bought it a few weeks ago and it's still going!
Title: Very Tasty

ReviewText: Since buying this I've stopped buying coffee in the coffee shops in work. I work in the Airport so I have many places to choose from. I have actually saved myself a fortune. It totally Rocks.

ReviewText: I first tried this at a friend's house and was immediately hooked! I thought it was freshly ground coffee, until I was shown the container. It has a rich, full-bodied flavour. Superb!

ReviewText: I have been buying azera for a while and intenso is definitely the best instant coffee I've ever had! Very high quality with no bitter taste and pretty smooth to go down too!

ReviewText: My wife bought this and I was a bit sceptical as to its flavour. How wrong I was it was flavoursome rich and intense. I cannot wait to try the espresso.
